      <title>&#127919; Composite Risk Score Explained</title>
      <html>
        <![CDATA[
        <div style="padding: 20px; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border-radius: 8px;">
          <p style="color: #ccc; margin: 0 0 15px 0;">The <strong style="color: #53A051;">Composite Risk Score</strong> is a single 0-100 metric that aggregates multiple security factors into one executive-friendly number. <strong>Higher is better.</strong></p>
          
          <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; color: #ccc;">
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #333;">
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 10px; color: #6DB7C6;">Component</th>
              <th style="text-align: center; padding: 10px; color: #6DB7C6;">Weight</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 10px; color: #6DB7C6;">Description</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 10px; color: #6DB7C6;">How to Improve</th>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #222;">
              <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Rating Score</strong></td>
              <td style="text-align: center; padding: 10px;">40%</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Average security rating across portfolio (normalized from 0-900 scale)</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Remediate critical findings, improve configuration security</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #222;">
              <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Portfolio Health</strong></td>
              <td style="text-align: center; padding: 10px;">25%</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Percentage of companies meeting 640+ threshold</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Focus on underperforming vendors, escalate to procurement</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #222;">
              <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Findings Score</strong></td>
              <td style="text-align: center; padding: 10px;">20%</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Inverse of critical/severe open findings count</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Prioritize critical findings, assign remediation owners</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>SLA Compliance</strong></td>
              <td style="text-align: center; padding: 10px;">15%</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Percentage of findings remediated within SLA targets</td>
              <td style="padding: 10px;">Track MTTR metrics, improve remediation processes</td>
            </tr>
          </table>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 20px; display: flex; gap: 20px;">
            <div style="flex: 1; padding: 15px; background: rgba(83,160,81,0.2); border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;">
              <div style="font-size: 24px; color: #53A051; font-weight: bold;">75-100</div>
              <div style="color: #53A051;">Excellent</div>
